import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['miles'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['gas'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Mileage')
    plt.title('How has the average gas mileage changed over time?')
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Gas Mileage')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Miles Driven')
    ax.set_ylabel('Gas Mileage')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between miles driven and gas mileage?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('side').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.bar(data['side'], data['counts'], color=['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of driving on different sides of the road?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
